    "narrative": "The top play for the Austin Waves today is clearly **Gunnar Henderson** (74.06), whose elite leadoff position and favorable matchup against Warren provide the highest floor of the slate. He is closely followed by **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (72.39) and **Drake Baldwin** (71.82). While **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** faces a respectable arm in Woods Richardson, his raw talent profile remains our primary engine for runs and RBI. **Drake Baldwin** earns a massive boost today due to the suspect 5.47 xERA of Quintana; combined with a prime #2 spot in the order, he represents a high-efficiency start for the catcher slot. We are also monitoring the matchup for **Josh Lowe** (71.68) against Christian Scott; the extreme 15.44 xERA attached to that opponent makes **Josh Lowe** and **Nolan Schanuel** essential starts despite the uncertainty of their confirmed batting order positions.\n\nOur most difficult decision came at the utility spot, where **Josh Jung** (56.18) narrowly missed the cut. While **Josh Jung** carries enough pop to warrant consideration, the efficiency scores for **Nolan Schanuel** and **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.**\u2014the latter benefiting from a +14% platoon edge against Misiorowski\u2014ultimately pushed the optimizer toward a more aggressive stance on the top-half of the order. Meanwhile, **Heliot Ramos** (59.03) remains a start primarily for his stolen base potential; his matchup against a difficult southpaw like McClanahan is mitigated by his high sprint speed and a 100% stolen base rate against slow-delivering pitchers, fitting our philosophy of over-weighting speed in 5x5 Roto formats.\n\nWe are flagging **Miguel Vargas** and **Josh Lowe** as \"Lineup Pending\" risks; should either drop significantly in the batting order, their base projections will erode, potentially necessitating a pivot to **Marcell Ozuna** or **Brady House** from the bench. Furthermore, **Kyle Tucker** and **Andy Pages** are facing Liberatore, a lefty who represents the most significant SP hurdle on our scorecard today. Despite the strong projected scores, we will keep a close watch on the early innings to ensure that our aggressive reliance on **Jacob Wilson** and **Heliot Ramos** at the top of the order isn't stifled by early-game pitching dominance.",
